--liquibase formatted sql

--changeset cms-team:017-therapist-profiles
--comment: Populate therapist bios/scheduling/pronouns from brazentherapy.org profiles, tag specialties, publish

-- therapist_terms uses (therapist_id, term_id); inserts guarded so re-runs do not duplicate.

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Have you ever experienced a difficulty that left you feeling isolated, or found yourself in a relationship that just didn’t make sense? These experiences are deeply human, yet they can leave us feeling unsettled, disconnected, confused, and hurt. I genuinely enjoy connecting with people, hearing their stories, and supporting them through life’s more complex and vulnerable moments.

Above all else, my goal is to create a safe, affirming space where clients feel secure enough to speak openly about all parts of themselves. I am kink-affirming and sex-positive, and I welcome clients whose identities, relationships, or experiences may not fit within traditional norms. I prioritize trust, direct communication, and authenticity in the therapeutic relationship, believing that meaningful growth begins when people feel truly seen and respected.

In my work, I use a systemic lens to help individuals and partners develop a strong sense of self, build secure and satisfying relationships, and support overall emotional wellbeing. I specialize in working with LGBTQ+ individuals, those navigating anxiety and depression, neurodivergent clients, family-of-origin concerns, and people in polyamorous or consensually non-monogamous relationships.

Clients who tend to benefit most from working with me appreciate a candid, respectful, and collaborative approach. Therapy with me is not about judgment or quick fixes, but about increasing insight, strengthening resilience, and building self-trust at a pace that feels right for you.

In addition to my clinical work, I am a Board-Approved Clinical Supervisor in the state of Arizona and am licensed to practice in Arizona, Colorado, Minnesota, and Missouri. If this sounds like a good fit, I would love to connect and talk about how I can support you in reaching your goals.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://www.brazentherapy.org/contact', credentials = 'LPC' WHERE id = '090f35b3-caef-412d-806d-e0b11229735d';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I’m very proud of you for taking the first step of your healing journey! My approach is supportive and collaborative, using a trauma informed and strength based perspective in hopes of creating a safe environment that allows you to be transparent and work towards restoration. I have experience working with anxiety, depression, grief and other trauma related issues. Together we will navigate difficulties, challenges and transitions in order to help you live a more whole life.

We will use our time together using CBT, DBT skills, EMDR, IFS and mindfulness based therapies and motivational interviewing to reframe negative beliefs and develop new habits to replace old ones that no longer serve you.

Life isn’t always easy, and I’m honored to walk alongside you in the rough parts and celebrate your achievements!', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1927107', credentials = 'LCSW' WHERE id = '48eebf38-7398-46d8-9c2b-23fc30a048b3';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I am a licensed clinical social worker (LCSW) with over 10 years of experience in social work and an innate passion for helping others. I have had the pleasure of assisting countless families and individuals from birth to end of life in navigating hardships mentally, physically, and financially. I have worked on all levels of social work through supervision, case management, therapy, and policy work; everywhere from homes, hospitals, to the state capitol. My drive to help others has led me to therapy and directly supporting others in their healing journey. My passion for service is especially directed at black, brown, and queer folks. I understand there is power in being heard, seen and validated and I pride myself in allowing my clients the space for that.

I use a combination of Eye movement desensitization reprocessing (EMDR), motivational interviewing (MI), parts work/inner child work, dialectical behavioral therapy (DBT), solution focused therapy (SFT), and mindfulness to help people navigate trauma, anxiety, depression, self esteem, relationships, and other issues.

As we develop our therapeutic relationship, we will work together to understand your personal and generational history so you can move forward with compassion for your experiences but also work towards desired change. I honor my clients right to self determination and to be the “captain of their ship”; while I assist with direction from time to time.

I hope to move all my clients towards a deeper level of self love, self care and self compassion. If you are considering me to support you on your healing journey, please reach out for a 15 minute consultation.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/', credentials = 'LCSW' WHERE id = '4ecc0e80-5d6e-4c88-932f-af5a0fbbb3a6';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Hello! I''m Shuheng Hu, a Licensed Professional Counselor-Supervisor, holding a Master''s degree in Rehabilitation and Mental Health Counseling from the University of Arizona. I offer bilingual therapy services in English and Mandarin (普通话).

My practice is open to individuals from diverse backgrounds, enabling me to offer unique perspectives and support tailored to your personal growth. My therapeutic approach is eclectic, incorporating trauma-informed care, dialectical behavior therapy, cognitive behavioral therapy, psychodynamic therapy, acceptance and commitment therapy, and person-centered therapy. I have a specialization in managing complex trauma, depression, anxiety, work stress, life transitions, identity development, self-esteem issues, and the unique challenges faced by immigrants and minorities. I also address career indecision and relationship conflicts.

Clients who choose to work with me tend to feel that they could benefit from deep inquiry into existing problems and their origins. I value the trust you place in therapy and am committed to meeting you wherever you are in your journey. I truly respect your decision to seek therapy and I welcome you to reach out.
.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/', credentials = 'LPC' WHERE id = '37de7b68-5883-497e-845d-3ded9e0ad11d';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I provide a safe and affirming space for teens (15+) and adults navigating change, building confidence, and working through life’s challenges. With over 20 years of experience in healthcare and behavioral health, I help clients manage depression, anxiety, self-esteem concerns, relationship challenges, identity exploration, and major life transitions.

My approach is collaborative, supportive, and tailored to each person. I draw from CBT, DBT, ACT, and motivational interviewing, while maintaining a non-judgmental and affirming space for all clients, including those in the LGBTQIA+ community.

My focus is on meeting each client where they are, using evidence-based practices to help navigate challenges, strengthen resilience, and create meaningful progress toward personal goals. Clients often describe me as easy to talk to, compassionate, and focused on helping them find practical tools for growth and healing.

Specialties
• Depression
• Anxiety
• Self-Esteem
• Life Transitions

• Age: Teens (15+), Adults

Offers Letters for Gender Affirming Care: This clinician can write letters for those wanting insurance to cover gender affirming care costs or if a procedure requires one. One session, no pre-existing sessions necessary. Client must be 18+', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1894714', credentials = 'LAC' WHERE id = 'e04c3166-7b66-422e-bdf6-a1f602fdd206';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'As a Licensed Associate Counselor with a Master’s degree in Counseling, I’m passionate about helping clients feel seen, understood, and supported as they navigate life’s challenges. I work with adults (18+) experiencing anxiety, depression, trauma, grief and loss, relationship conflicts, and major life transitions.

My therapeutic approach is integrative, drawing from person-centered, cognitive-behavioral (CBT), dialectical behavior (DBT), and mindfulness-based techniques within a trauma-informed framework. I believe that healing begins with feeling safe and connected — that therapy should be a space where you can show up as you are and explore what healing looks like for you.

In our work together, my goal is to help you reconnect with your strengths, develop new tools for emotional balance, and move toward a more grounded and fulfilling life. I also offer sessions in Spanish and welcome individuals from all backgrounds.

If you’re ready to begin your healing journey, I’d be honored to walk alongside you. Let’s take the next step together.

Como Consejera Asociada Licenciada con una Maestría en Consejería, me apasiona ayudar a mis clientes a sentirse vistos, comprendidos y apoyados mientras navegan los desafíos de la vida. Trabajo con adultos (18+) que experimentan ansiedad, depresión, trauma, duelo y pérdida, conflictos en las relaciones y transiciones importantes en la vida.

Mi enfoque terapéutico es integrador, basado en técnicas centradas en la persona, cognitivo-conductuales (TCC), de conducta dialéctica (TCD) y de atención plena (mindfulness), dentro de un marco informado por el trauma. Creo que la sanación comienza al sentirse seguro y conectado — que la terapia debe ser un espacio donde puedas presentarte tal como eres y explorar qué significa sanar para ti.

En nuestro trabajo juntos, mi objetivo es ayudarte a reconectarte con tus fortalezas, desarrollar nuevas herramientas para el equilibrio emocional y avanzar hacia una vida más estable y plena. También ofrezco sesiones en español y doy la bienvenida a personas de todos los orígenes.

Si estás listo para comenzar tu proceso de sanación, sería un honor acompañarte en este camino. Demos juntos el siguiente paso.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1913549', credentials = 'LAC' WHERE id = '0f3fc021-3883-4415-9b89-430472fd0f65';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I’m Aundrea Austin, a Licensed Master of Social Work (LMSW) with a deep passion for supporting individuals and families through meaningful therapeutic work. I earned my degrees from Arizona State University and Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis, and I’m proud to bring a diverse range of experiences to my practice. I''m originally from Chicago but spent most of my life in Arizona. I’ve been dedicated to working with youth since high school, always driven by my dream of becoming a therapist. My career journey began in classrooms and out-of-school programs for school-aged children. A pivotal experience was my time working with youth and families at the Boys & Girls Clubs of Indianapolis, where I also served two years with AmeriCorps. I realized my calling to pursue social work and shape my desire to better understand and address the unique needs of my community.

Over the years, I’ve enjoyed working with children, adolescents, and transitioning young adults. However, my dedication to families and community allows me to work effectively with individuals of all ages and backgrounds. My therapeutic approach integrates foundational interventions like Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) and Solution-Focused Brief Therapy (SFBT), alongside mindfulness techniques and Expressive Arts Therapy (EAT).

I believe in working from a strengths-based perspective, helping individuals recognize and build on their personal strengths, skills, and achievements. In our work together, you can expect to develop adaptive coping strategies through both verbal and nonverbal methods. I prioritize listening closely to my clients, meeting you where you are, and providing the support needed to help you take steps toward personal growth. If you''re ready to embark on a journey of healing and self-improvement, I look forward to collaborating with you with an open mind and heart.

Ages:
Adults

Children (8+)
Adolescents', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1730379', credentials = 'LMSW' WHERE id = '6821799d-24cb-4f53-a7ee-8d2099f1a38b';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I’m passionate about helping adults navigate symptoms of anxiety, depression, family dysfunction, and insecure attachment. Many of the people I work with find themselves stuck in patterns of people-pleasing or self-criticism — trying to hold it all together while feeling disconnected inside.

My approach is warm, collaborative, and trauma-informed. I integrate person-centered therapy with cognitive-behavioral, somatic, and mindfulness-based approaches throughout the healing process. Together, we’ll work to quiet the inner critic, explore patterns that no longer serve you, and build a more compassionate relationship with yourself.

At the heart of my work is the belief that healing begins through connection — to yourself, to others, and to your own story. So many of us have learned to perform, to please, or to shrink ourselves just to get by. I see therapy as a safe space to unlearn those patterns and rediscover your authentic self. It can be a place to breathe deeply, let go, and start fresh. If you feel this aligns with your needs, I welcome you to reach out.

Ages:

Adults 20 yrs +', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/', credentials = 'LMSW' WHERE id = 'd267623f-fcd6-4950-8796-6f5e6714937d';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Welcome, and thanks for stopping by. Struggling with transitions? No need to make therapy another one. I offer support by helping you work through tough times and learn how to cope with stressors if/when they show up. I also support those who have experienced trauma, foster care, homelessness, shifts in identity, domestic/interpersonal violence, the criminal justice system, and loss/grief.

I strive to make therapy an enjoyable and fulfilling experience and meet clients where they are at in their healing journey. I emphasize the use of client centered and strength based approaches. I also prioritize the preservation of self, relationships, and family. Those who benefit most from working with me appreciate a direct and compassionate therapist. I incorporate the use of trauma informed care, mindfulness techniques, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT), Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR), and expressive arts.

I moved across the country (Wisconsin to Arizona) and personally understand that transitions can be difficult. I also come from a multicultural background and understand how the overlap of culture/race can impact an individual especially in the therapeutic process. This is why it is essential for me to create a safe space for my clients as they embark on their healing journey. I have been in the social work field for over 9 years and have had the pleasure of serving a wide range of populations and I welcome those from all walks of life. Don''t forget to schedule your free 15 minute consultation! I look forward to being a part of your therapy journey!

Ages: Children (10+), Teens, and Adults', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1566667', credentials = 'LMSW' WHERE id = '1e724c1e-d97c-4208-8513-8961b1916129';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Hi, I''m Riana. If you''ve spent most of your life feeling like your emotions are too much or like you''re constantly bracing for something to go wrong, you''re not broken. You''re probably just exhausted from carrying more than most people realize. I work with adults who grew up having to figure things out on their own, often because the people who were supposed to be there for them were unreliable. Maybe your parents or caretaker was unpredictable, dismissive, selfish, or just emotionally unavailable. That kind of upbringing leaves scars not just in your memories but how your nervous system reacts and how you relate to the world.

I don''t just hand you a worksheet and call it therapy. I''m genuinely present with you in session which means I''m also paying attention to what''s happening in your body and not just your words. I''ll teach you grounding skills from DBT without rushing through it to check a box but actually using it in session to learn how to ride out an overwhelming emotion.

If any of this felt familiar, or if the world has been a lot lately and you''re not sure where else to take it, reach out to me! I''m accepting new clients and offer a free 15 minute consultation to make sure we''re a good fit.

Ages:
Teens (16+)
Adults (18+)', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1875151', credentials = 'LCSW' WHERE id = '7dd7ca33-9eff-4d77-bae2-e8f28da2680a';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Hi there, my name is Alex! I’m so honored to have you here, thank you for speaking up and asking for help. Anxiety, depression, suicidal thoughts, and trauma can all hover like a dark cloud, impacting self-talk, relationships with others, and your sense of purpose.

I primarily work with teenagers, adults, and youth as young as eight navigating depression, anxiety, relationship difficulties, and trauma. I specialize in men’s issues, teenagers struggling with emotion regulation, and young adults trying to acclimate to life outside of childhood.

My therapeutic approach mainly draws from mindfulness-based practices to help you stay more present, Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) to help challenge and reframe unhelpful thought patterns, and Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT) to learn how to manage difficult and distressing emotions. I also utilize Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing (EMDR) to help you heal from past traumas.

The most important thing is for you to find a therapist that feels right. My clients should expect a sincere, transparent, and collaborative approach. Therapy is a space where you do not need to hide who you are. Come as you are, and I will meet you there.

Ages:
Children and Teens: 8+

Adults: 18+

Elders: 65+', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1869077', credentials = 'LMSW' WHERE id = '61e0e535-7c48-4d2b-8311-302d65f87e42';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Are you feeling overwhelmed, anxious, stuck, or navigating a major life transition? Perhaps your child is struggling with emotional regulation, behavior challenges, self-esteem, or adjusting to changes at home, school, or within relationships. Whether you’re seeking support for yourself, your child, or your family, therapy can provide a safe space to better understand your experiences, build coping skills, and create meaningful change. I work with children ages 7 and older, adolescents, and adults experiencing concerns such as anxiety, depression, stress, life transitions, emotional regulation difficulties, self-esteem challenges, relationship concerns, and adjustment-related issues. My goal is to create a supportive, collaborative environment where clients feel heard, valued, and empowered.

My therapeutic approach is grounded in collaboration, authenticity, and meeting each client where they are. I draw from Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) to help clients identify and challenge unhelpful thought patterns while developing practical skills to manage emotions and navigate daily challenges. I also incorporate expressive arts and play therapy techniques, particularly when working with children and adolescents, to encourage self-expression, creativity, and emotional processing in developmentally appropriate ways.

As a Filipina, first generation immigrant, therapist, I understand how culture, family dynamics, identity, and community can shape the way we experience mental health and healing. Growing up in a culture where mental health conversations were often limited has deepened my appreciation for creating spaces where people feel comfortable discussing their emotions without judgment. My background in social work, mental health, education, and youth advocacy has strengthened my commitment to providing compassionate, culturally responsive care. If you’re interested in learning more about working together, I invite you to schedule a free 15-minute consultation to see if we’re a good fit.

Ages:

Children, teens, adolescents, adults

Languages:

English, Tagalog', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1869074', credentials = 'LMSW' WHERE id = '3b5ffc1f-f700-46d1-a111-000bbaef3d03';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Hi, I’m Cailin! I’m so glad you’re here. You’ve been trying to manage it all, but lately it feels heavier. The stress, self-doubt, and relationship issues keep piling up. Anxiety and ongoing worry might keep you overthinking, past experiences may still affect how you connect with others, or family dynamics might feel complicated.

I support teens, adults, couples, and families facing anxiety, trauma, relationship challenges, LGBTQIA+ issues, or difficult past experiences. My therapeutic approach primarily draws from relational work, EFT, EMDR, and parts work to help you explore your emotions, build self-awareness, and find ways to make meaningful progress at your own pace.

Finding the right therapist is such a personal process. I bring authenticity to sessions and enjoy working with clients who want the same. I support people seeking more than talk therapy, real change, and those who find it hard to express feelings or needs. Let''s connect through a free 15-minute consultation to see if it feels like the right fit for you.

Populations:

Couples
Teens (14+)

Adults (18+)
Elderly (65+)

Offers Letters for Gender Affirming Care: This clinician can write letters for those wanting insurance to cover gender affirming care costs or if a procedure requires one. One session, no pre-existing sessions necessary. Client must be 18+', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/', credentials = 'LAMFT' WHERE id = '4c081b85-bb59-4497-80c9-3ef1df0a859f';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I’m Erica Marisella Harris, a Licensed Professional Counselor and Clinical Supervisor with a Master’s degree in Professional Counseling from Grand Canyon University. With over a decade of experience, I specialize in working with children, teens, and adults navigating complex trauma, PTSD, neurodivergence (including Autism and ADHD), and anxiety and depression. I’m also a proud LGBTQ+ ally and advocate for inclusive, affirming care.

Therapy with me is a collaborative, creative, and compassionate process. I believe healing begins in a space where you can be fully yourself—without judgment. Clients often tell me they feel safe and understood from our very first session. As someone who is neurodivergent and a little quirky myself, I bring authenticity, humor, and flexibility into my work.

I blend evidence-based practices like Trauma-Focused CBT, DBT, and traditional CBT with expressive tools such as gameplay, sand tray, and storytelling to meet you where you are—especially if you''ve felt stuck or unseen in more conventional talk therapy settings. My approach is personalized, playful when appropriate, and always rooted in helping you build a life that aligns with your values and strengths.

Whether this is your first time seeking therapy or you''re returning to it, I’m here to help you feel supported, empowered, and truly heard.

Outside the therapy room, I enjoy playing tennis, spending time with loved ones (including furry ones), and unwinding with a good movie or show.

Ages:

Children

Teens

Adults (18+)

Offers Letters for Gender Affirming Care: This clinician can write letters for those wanting insurance to cover gender affirming care costs or if a procedure requires one. One session, no pre-existing sessions necessary. Client must be 10+', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1869631', credentials = 'LPC' WHERE id = 'b5fe2a7b-c2d0-4bb0-a6c6-2908df488579';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Are you seeking a healing space that honors all of you—mind, body, and spirit? I’m Vonyee Soulfire, a holistic therapist, yoga teacher, and somatic practitioner-in-training. With 15+ years of experience in the school system and 32 years of living yoga and holistic health, I support individuals and families in healing trauma, anxiety, and emotional disconnection through integrative care.

My practice blends Carl Jung’s depth psychology, Dialectical Behavior Therapy (DBT), and neuroscience-informed somatic therapy. As a Liberian-born African-American woman, mother, and intuitive guide, I offer a culturally grounded, spiritually rich space that nurtures your transformation. Healing isn’t just a clinical journey—it’s a soul calling.

Whether you’re navigating life transitions, burnout, emotional overwhelm, or simply seeking to return home to yourself, I offer a therapeutic space rooted in embodiment, alignment, and truth. I believe in matching language with energy, emotions with movement, and behavior with intention. Our work may include mindful dialogue, breathwork, body-based techniques, and inner child exploration.

Currently completing my somatic certification and preparing to begin my PhD in holistic psychology, my commitment to healing is lifelong. I walk this path with you.

When I’m not working, I enjoy hiking, swimming, cuddling with my cat, and restoring myself in nature. Let’s begin your journey home—together.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&clinicianId=1875810', credentials = 'LAC' WHERE id = 'f3491218-a0f2-42e8-b1c7-4559dd60d876';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'I am deeply dedicated to guiding individuals and couples through some of life’s most complex relational challenges. Whether you’re working through infidelity, emotional distance, intimacy concerns, communication struggles, or a fading sense of connection, I offer a grounded and supportive space for insight, growth, and repair. Alongside couples therapy, I support individuals in resolving conflict and cultivating healthier, more secure dynamics within their most significant relationships.

I have dedicated myself to creating a safe and affirming space for individuals and couples who identify as queer and non-monogamous. My passion for supporting diverse relationships stems from a deep commitment to inclusivity and a belief in the inherent value of all forms of love. Love is Love.

Seeking support takes courage, especially when life feels overwhelming or you’re struggling to hold everything together on your own. Whether you’re facing anxiety, relationship challenges, identity questions, or simply feeling stuck — you don’t have to navigate it alone. In our work together, I offer a safe, nonjudgmental space where you can be fully you!

Ages:
Adults
Couples/Families', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://clientsecure.me/widget-redirect?scopeId=93f13a01-cc87-478e-9773-a7b940db5cb8&applicationId=7c72cb9f9a9b913654bb89d6c7b4e71a77911b30192051da35384b4d0c6d505b&channel=client_portal&appearance=%7B%22fullScreen%22%3Atrue%7D&contact=true&clinicianId=1363028', credentials = 'LAMFT' WHERE id = 'a162fec5-6e25-4cfc-876c-5d2f3ed1caff';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Hello! My name is Chelsea. I earned my master’s degree in counseling psychology with a specialization in couple and family therapy from the University of Colorado Denver, and I am a Licensed Professional Counselor and Licensed Addiction Counselor. My primary focus is working with individuals and those in relationships, addressing a wide range of concerns such as depression, anxiety, substance use, multicultural and social justice issues, and maintaining stable mental health.

My approach to therapy centers on creating a safe and nonjudgmental environment. I use systemic, multicultural, and strengths-based perspectives to help clients identify and work toward their goals. My style is warm, grounded, and collaborative, blending insight with practical tools. I use Cognitive Behavioral Therapy to work with thought and behavior patterns, parts work to build internal understanding, and attachment and systems perspectives to explore how identity, culture, and relationships shape your experience. We will also develop and practice skills for coping, boundaries, and communication.

Taking the first step can be difficult when shame, time, cost, or past experiences get in the way. I am committed to social justice and to tailoring care to your values, needs, and goals. Together, we can address what’s holding you back, create a realistic plan, and track progress over time. If you’re ready for support, I invite you to reach out to see if we’re a good fit.', published = TRUE, scheduling_url = 'https://brazentherapy.clientsecure.me/', credentials = 'LPC, LIAC' WHERE id = '6f894a93-af89-4e47-b2a4-fc8a6b1121a4';

UPDATE therapists SET bio = 'Do you have sudden shifts in mood, intense emotions, or overwhelm leading to shut down? Do you find yourself constantly on edge or consumed by worry? These experiences can be extremely isolating. Perhaps you''ve tried to build connection with others, but lacked the words to describe your internal thoughts and feelings, leading to frustration and detachment. If you are seeking an affirming space where you can explore your world safely, I would be honored to partner with you. I provide detailed psychoeducation throughout therapy, ensuring that you can always understand the "why" behind symptoms and treatments.

I utilize EMDR, DBT, and parts work (informed by Internal Family Systems). These treatments are complimented by my lived experience as a queer, neurodivergent therapist. In session, I approach your stories with curiosity. You are the expert on your life, and I bring the mental health knowledge. Together, we can pursue healing and growth in your life.

In my life outside of therapy, I enjoy playing board games and D&D with my friends, watching Formula 1, or reading a good novel. My favorite quote from Anthony Doerr’s, All the Light We Cannot See, sums up my counseling philosophy: “Why else do any of this if not to become who we want to be?

Ages:
